<emphasis id="204CB1187441020B099B029E80FF35F8" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="153">Muhlenbergia flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was allied with 
<taxonomicName id="074D8570E2CF938FD5EF8B1A52408838" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. flaviseta" order="Poales" pageId="30" pageNumber="153" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="flaviseta">
<emphasis id="1B0010918D0FC0A64F7BA0F4CF4301E6" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="153">M. flaviseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Scribn. and 
<taxonomicName id="40273D95498095D8226B2704ED8584BB" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. watsoniana" order="Poales" pageId="30" pageNumber="153" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="watsoniana">
<emphasis id="D80FC6473FC783257C0E1432FEA49648" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="153">M. watsoniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hitchc. (≡ 
<taxonomicName id="A64448374A83036859FB6DBBC0D5DCC4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. scabra" order="Poales" pageId="30" pageNumber="153" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="scabra">
<emphasis id="090A7C02D95C90B60EEE8C7A81D13BD1" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="153">M. scabra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
S. Watson), since all have 
<pageBreakToken id="E90405A1D58A11E0F0FB75E019C9A871" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" start="start">short</pageBreakToken>
flat blades, spike-like 
<emphasis id="39919567F895AF626EF822F914C97FF9" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">panicles</emphasis>
and slender flexuous awns. However, 
<taxonomicName id="CC1E11ED0C88E4A4B5A4872DD4CD99DE" authorityName="Scribn" authorityYear="1897" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia flaviseta" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="flaviseta">
<emphasis id="906451A1D4E9C121A1D6E49225F34430" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">Muhlenbergia flaviseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3C054191CE046FDC057EE953E584A26A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. watsoniana" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="watsoniana">
<emphasis id="F387FE927F6F6DE19119D361CFCF8449" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">M. watsoniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are members of the 
<taxonomicName id="D8CA97713D11A533FFB1A4371A45C5B6" authority="subg. Clomena" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="subg." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M." order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus" subGenus="Clomena">M. subg. Clomena</taxonomicName>
clade while 
<taxonomicName id="9991653F0E0E7BFBC26356C09E56F7E1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. flexuosa" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis id="DFFF0D1070FCBC99F693AD82D2664716" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">M. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to 
<taxonomicName id="421BCCFBC0B2927FEC5355F91CC7B02C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. plumiseta" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="plumiseta">
<emphasis id="D23972A965EB3521EFB78F1E1C574701" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">M. plumiseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Columbus- 
<taxonomicName id="40A340A3E78CE9A2F9CA4AF12DA36860" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. pereilema" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pereilema">
<emphasis id="532AA94C134E222BD267560F14BE69E7" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">M. pereilema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
P.M. Peterson- 
<taxonomicName id="C426AE50C8E541B973387DA1DBCDBB01" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. beyrichiana" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="beyrichiana">
<emphasis id="6714478CE9902B45BAE8B77A6197F151" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">M. beyrichiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade, all of which are included in 
<taxonomicName id="4886914F2EF007B512019EB5D934DF32" authority="subg. Muhlenbergi" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="subg." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M." order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus" subGenus="Muhlenbergi">M. subg. Muhlenbergi</taxonomicName>
a (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6E15465907051A137EF99690D447A18F" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. A, B Maximum-likelihood tree inferred from combined plastid (ndhA intron, rps 16 - trnK, rps 16 intron, rps 3, and rpl 32 - trnL) and ITS sequences. Thick branches indicate posterior probabilities of 0.95 - 1; species in red occur in South America; scale bar = 2 %." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.114.28799.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/254042" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">1</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2D7C608B0A31736DFBCA315B966B0545" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="59" pageNumber="182" pagination="1532 - 1554" refId="B38" refString="Peterson, PM, Romaschenko, K, Johnson, G, 2010b. A phylogeny and classification of the Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae) based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences. American Journal of Botany 97 (9): 1532 - 1554, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" title="A phylogeny and classification of the Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae) based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" volume="97" year="2010 b">Peterson et al. 2010b</bibRefCitation>
). Within 
<taxonomicName id="3226CEC3F92C0F0FF74377956B3CB51F" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Muhlenbergia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Muhlenbergia" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="31D6CC1AC3A12A6773E93A29E7C7F5CB" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">Muhlenbergia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the derivation of a slender flexuous awn found in 
<taxonomicName id="91ED655A4082FF6DE5CFA5151B3533AF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M. flexuosa" order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="flexuosa">
<emphasis id="29E87D91B7585684E73F345403E123FD" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">M. flexuosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has occurred in four of the five subgenera currently recognised within the genus and is only lacking in 
<taxonomicName id="DF40F9026E4544D792B870ACEDC4AF89" authority="subg. Pseudosporobolus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="M." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="subg." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="M." order="Poales" pageId="31" pageNumber="154" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus" subGenus="Pseudosporobolus">M. subg. Pseudosporobolus</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="42B1EEF6E7F6C298DCEFB5D3F87E753C" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. A, B Maximum-likelihood tree inferred from combined plastid (ndhA intron, rps 16 - trnK, rps 16 intron, rps 3, and rpl 32 - trnL) and ITS sequences. Thick branches indicate posterior probabilities of 0.95 - 1; species in red occur in South America; scale bar = 2 %." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.114.28799.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/254042" pageId="31" pageNumber="154">1B</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="59565C8912D5503314DECD0BBDE8F271" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" author="Peterson, PM" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="59" pageNumber="182" pagination="1532 - 1554" refId="B38" refString="Peterson, PM, Romaschenko, K, Johnson, G, 2010b. A phylogeny and classification of the Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae) based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences. American Journal of Botany 97 (9): 1532 - 1554, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" title="A phylogeny and classification of the Muhlenbergiinae (Poaceae: Chloridoideae: Cynodonteae) based on plastid and nuclear DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.3732/ajb.0900359" volume="97" year="2010 b">Peterson et al. 2010b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
